The offices include kindergarten, architects understood
The Avriopoint administration building in Brno is the new headquarters of Arch.Design.
No one would expect him to hide a mini-school girl with everything that goes with it - with colorful walls, imaginative furniture, a bunch of toys and even a miniature playground on the outdoor terrace.
Since October last year she can be visited by children of Arch.Design employees.
Arch.Design, the design-architectonic company, whose studios produced a number of important Brno buildings, has been counting on the space for its company mini-school since the first drawings of Avriopoint building.
She employs almost 90 people, mostly at the age of babyboom, and she cared so that women designers and architects could return to work quickly.
Together with the possibility of abbreviated work, kindergarten is a benefit that Arch.Design offers to its employees within the social program.
Builders and architects thus have the opportunity to combine demanding employment with child care.
Arch.Design employees invented the mini-school and managed to obtain a subsidy from the European Union and the Ministry of Labour and Social Affairs with the support of management.
The corporate mini-school is financed by the European Social Fund through the Operational Programme Human Resources and Employment and the state budget of the Czech Republic.
Thanks to grant financing (subsidisation of CZK 2.8 million), they were able to purchase equipment and equipment and provide qualified staff and operation for two years.
After the financial subsidy has been exhausted (2 years), Arch.Design has an obligation to operate a mini-school for 3 years at its own expense.
The preparation of the project lasted one year and with the request for a subsidy was significantly helped by Economy Rating.
The care is provided by qualified staff, the children are looked after daily by the nurse and teacher of the school, so children can attend kindergarten without age limit, yet most of them are over 3 years old.
Because it is a "minimum school", only 5 children can be present at the same time, but more can be replaced during the day.
The operation of the kindergarten is flexible according to the needs of the parents and the children of all employees have the same right to use the kindergarten regardless of the hierarchy of position in the company.
Although it is individual education and care, the programme is comparable to the framework programme of pre-school education.
Children not only play here, but they are also provided with quality teaching - from basic recognition to preparation to school benches, the English language is also taught.
The class is equipped not only with toys, stimulating games, but also with a computer that children can use.
